IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: A TRADE ASSOCIATION ORGANIZED TO ASSIST, INFORM, & EDUCATE ITS MEMBERS WHO CONSIST OF COMMERICIAL BANKS, THRIFT INSTITUTIONS & TRUST COMPANIES IN TN.
IRS990.MissionDescription: THE MISSION OF THE TENNESSEE BANKERS ASSOCIATION IS TO REPRESENT AND SUPPORT ITS MEMBERS, ENABLING THEM TO PROVIDE A FULL RANGE OF QUALITY FINANCIAL PRODUCTS AND SERVICES WHILE MAINTAINING SAFETY AND SOUNDNESS.
IRS990.Description: 63 EDUCATIONAL SEMINARS ARE PROVIDED FOR BANKERS AND ASSOCIATE MEMBERS IN TENNESSEE. THE SEMINARS HAD A TOTAL OF 6,074 ATTENDEES.

Activity2.Description: TENNESSEE BANKERS MAGAZINE PROVIDES 12 MONTHLY SUBSCRIPTIONS WITH CONTINUING UPDATES AND ARTICLES RELATING TO THE PROFESSION TO SUBSCRIBERS. THE MAGAZINE HAD 2,784 SUBSCRIBERS INCLUDING THOSE INCLUDED WITH MEMBERSHIP AT YEAR END.

Activity3.Description: TENNESSEE BANKERS ASSOCIATION GROUP INSURANCE FUND PROVIDES INSURANCE TO MEMBERS. THIS FUND WAS LIQUIDATED ON OCTOBER 31, 2009 DURING THE FISCAL YEAR.

Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.Explanation: THE COMPANY ADOPTED GUIDANCE ISSUED BY THE FASB WITH RESPECT TO ACCOUNTING FOR UNCERTAINTY IN INCOME TAXES AS OF MAY 1, 2009. A TAX POSITION IS RECOGNIZED AS A BENEFIT ONLY IF IT IS "MORE LIKELY THAN NOT" THAT THE TAX POSITION WOULD BE SUSTAINED IN A TAX EXAMINATION, WITH A TAX EXAMINATION BEING PRESUMED TO OCCUR. THE AMOUNT RECOGNIZED IS THE LARGEST AMOUNT OF TAX BENEFIT THAT IS GREATER THAN 50% LIKELY OF BEING REALIZED ON EXAMINATION. FOR TAX POSITIONS NOT MEETING THE "MORE LIKELY THAN NOT" TEST, NO TAX BENEFIT IS RECORDED. THE ADOPTION HAD NO AFFECT ON THE COMPANY'S FINANCIAL STATEMENTS.

Form990ScheduleJPartIII.Explanation: TRAVEL FOR COMPANIONS: SENIOR MANAGEMENT AND BOARD MEMBERS ARE PROVIDED TRAVEL FOR COMPANIONS WHEN THERE IS DEEMED TO BE A BONAFIDE BUSINESS PURPOSE WHICH BENEFITS THE ASSOCIATION. THE EXPENSES ARE REIMBURSED TO THE EMPLOYEE AND/OR BOARD MEMBER ONCE PROPER SUBSTANTATION HAS BEEN REMITTED. THESE PAYMENTS ARE NOT TAXABLE COMPENSATION TO THE EMPLOYEE OR BOARD MEMBER.
TAX INDEMNIFICATION AND GROSS-UP PAYMENTS: EMPLOYEE CHRISTMAS BONUSES ARE DISTRIBUTED TO ALL EMPLOYEES AND TAXABLE TO THE RECIPIENT.

Form990ScheduleJPartIII.Explanation: SOCIAL CLUB DUES OR INITIATION FEES: SOCIAL CLUB AND PRIVATE BUSINESS DINING CLUB MEMBERSHIPS ARE FOR BUSINESS USE AND AVAILABLE TO SENIOR MANAGEMENT. ALL ARE RELATED TO BUSINESS PURPOSES SO THEY ARE NOT TAXABLE TO EMPLOYEES.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Section A, Line 6
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE TENNESSEE BANKERS ASSOCIATION HAS 2 CLASSES OF MEMBERS: (1) REGULAR AND (2) ASSOCIATE. THE MEMBERS (OR THEIR DELEGATES) MAY ATTEND MEMBERSHIP MEETINGS AND VOTE AND PARTICIPATE IN THE BUSINESS OF SUCH MEETINGS. THE CHAIRMAN, CHAIRMAN-ELECT, AND VICE CHAIRMAN SHALL BE ELECTED BY THE REGULAR MEMBERS AT THE ANNUAL MEETING. IN ADDITION, THE BYLAWS MAY BE AMENDED AND VOTED ON BY THE DELEGATES AT THE ANNUAL MEETING.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Members or stockholders electing members of governing body
GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Section A, Line 7a
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: MEMBERS HAVE THE RIGHT TO VOICE VOTE IN ELECTION MATTERS AT THE ANNUAL MEETING. THE TENNESSEE BANKERS ASSOCIATION HAS 2 CLASSES OF MEMBERS: (1) REGULAR AND (2) ASSOCIATE. THE BY-LAWS MAY BE AMENDED AT ANY ANNUAL MEETING OR BY A WRITTEN BALLOT BY A VOTE OF TWO THIRDS OF THE DELEGATES PRESENT OR A MAJORITY OF THE VOTING POWER, WHICHEVER IS LESS, NOTICE OF THE PROPOSED AMENDMENT HAVING BEEN FIRST SUBMITTED TO THE SECRETARY.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Decisions requiring approval by members or stockholders
GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Section A, Line 7b
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE CHAIRMAN, CHAIRMAN ELECT, AND VICE-CHAIRMAN SHALL BE ELECTED BY THE REGULAR MEMBERS AT THE ANNUAL MEETING FOR A PERIOD OF ONE YEAR AND SHALL SERVE UNTIL THEIR SUCCESSORS ARE ELECTED.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Review of form 990 by governing body
GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 11A
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE FORM 990 AND ALL RELATED SCHEDULES ARE REVIEWED BY THE CONTROLLER, PRESIDENT, AND EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE OF THE TENNESSEE BANKERS ASSOCIATION BOARD OF DIRECTORS PRIOR TO FILING IT WITH THE IRS. AN ELECTRONIC COPY OF THE FINAL FORM 990 IS PROVIDED TO ALL MEMBERS OF THE ORGANIZATION'S GOVERNING BODY PRIOR TO FILING WITH THE IRS.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 12c
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS, OFFICERS, AND KEY EMPLOYEES MUST REVIEW AND SIGN A WRITTEN COPY OF THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY ON AN ANNUAL BASIS. SENIOR MANAGEMENT REVIEWS FOR CONFLICT DISCLOSURES AND NONE HAVE BEEN DISCLOSED, SUSPECTED, OR DISCOVERED. SHOULD THERE BE THE POSSIBILITY OF A CONFLICT, THE CONFLICT MAY BE RESOLVED BY HAVING THE DIRECTOR DISCLOSE TO THE CHAIRMAN, AND, IF NECESSARY THE ENTIRE BOARD, THE POSSIBILITY AND NATURE OF THE CONFLICT. AFTER DISCLOSURE, THE BOARD MEMBER MAY PARTICIPATE IN A DISCUSSION ON THE ISSUE. HOWEVER, THE DIRECTOR SHOULD ABSTAIN IN ANY VOTE ON THE MATTER. IN ORDER TO ASSURE COMPLIANCE WITH THE PROVISIONS OF THIS POLICY, IT IS THE DUTY OF EVERY DIRECTOR, OFFICER, AND EMPLOYEE TO BRING TO THE ATTENTION OF THE APPROPRIATE BOARD MEMBER, SENIOR OFFICER, OR SUPERVISOR, ANY VIOLATION OR POSSIBLE VIOLATION OF THIS POLICY. IT IS THE FURTHER DUTY OF THE PERSON SO NOTIFIED TO COMMUNICATE THE VIOLATION OR POTENTIAL VIOLATION TO THE PRESIDENT, OR IF THE VIOLATION IS BY THE PRESIDENT, TO THE CHAIRMAN OF THE BOARD, WHO SHALL INSTITUTE AN INVESTIGATION OF SUCH VIOLATION OR POTENTIAL VIOLATION. A VIOLATION OF THIS POLICY SHALL, AT THE DISCRETION OF THE BOARD, RESULT IN THE SUSPENSION OR TERMINATION OF THE DIRECTOR, OFFICER, OR EMPLOYEE INVOLVED.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Process used to establish compensation of top management official
GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 15a
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE COMPENSATION OF THE PRESIDENT IS REVIEWED BY THE COMPENSATION COMMITTEE AND VOTED ON BY THE FULL BOARD OF DIRECTORS. SALARY SURVEYS ARE UTILIZED AND SENT TO THE COMPENSATION COMMITTEE AND FULL BOARD FOR APPROVAL, AND CONTEMPORENEOUS DOCUMENTATION IS PERFORMED WITH REGARD TO THESE TRANSACTIONS. THE YEAR IN WHICH THIS PROCESS WAS LAST UNDERTAKEN WAS 2009.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Process used to establish compensation of other officers/key employees
GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 15b
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE COMPENSATION OF OTHER OFFICERS AND KEY EMPLOYEES IS REVIEWED BY THE COMPENSATION COMMITTEE AND VOTED ON BY THE FULL BOARD OF DIRECTORS. SALARY SURVEYS ARE UTILIZED AND SENT TO THE COMPENSATION COMMITTEE AND FULL BOARD FOR APPROVAL, AND CONTEMPORENEOUS DOCUMENTATION IS PERFORMED WITH REGARD TO THESE TRANSACTIONS. THE YEAR IN WHICH THIS PROCESS WAS LAST UNDERTAKEN WAS 2009.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, Line 19
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICIES, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE NOT REQUIRED DISCLOSURES PURSUANT TO INTERNAL REVENUE CODE (IRC) SECTION 6104. THESE DOCUMENTS ARE NOT AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC AT THIS TIME.
